The paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques for enhancing outdoor vision, which falls under the scope of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of adaptive filters, which is a common technique in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. The proposed method also involves efficient estimation of atmospheric light, which can be considered as an artificial intelligence (cs.AI) problem. Finally, the paper discusses the enhancement of textures and edges, which is a common problem in machine learning (cs.LG) research.
